tar  aThis book investigates the changing patterns of labour market and unemployment policies in EU member states during the period since fiscal austerity took hold in 2010 during the deepest postwar recession in Europe. Looking at the big European picture, do we see a convergence or a divergence in labour market and unemployment policy trends and outputs? Has labour market insecurity increased or decreased and can these changes be associated with the observed changes in labour market policies and macroeconomic conditions? Written by leading experts in the field, the book provides detailed national case studies from across the EU, which span labour market regimes and intensities of fiscal pressures to explore whether, and if so how, retrenchment or expansion have taken place across different types of labour market policies and how these changes have been distributed across the well-protected and the less well-protected labour market populations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh1 aAgostini, Chiara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBennett, Hayley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaune, Hélène, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidsson, Johan Bo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomonkos, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDukelow, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEichhorst, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHassel, Anke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeins, Elke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoogenboom, Marcel, econtribut